<p>My <code>recycler view</code> get a list of data from <code>youtube API</code> using <code>GSON</code> library. In one URL, the returned <code>JSON</code> is :</p>  <pre><code>items: [ { kind: "youtube#playlist", etag: ""tag/abc"", id: "id",  </code></pre>  <p>Notice that the id field is a <code>String</code></p>  <p>The problem is, the other URL return :</p>  <pre><code>items: [ { kind: "youtube#searchResult", etag: ""etag/abc"", id: { kind: "youtube#playlist", playlistId: "id" }, </code></pre>  <p>The id become a <code>Class</code>.</p>  <p>The simplest way is to create different <code>GSON</code> models and different <code>adapter</code> for the <code>recycler view</code>. However we will need to call <code>setAdapter</code> multiple time, which will impact the performance.</p>  <p>Do anyone have better workaround for this?</p>  <p>Thanks for your time  </p>